WEBVTT

00:01:46.666 --> 00:01:48.041
Thank you!

00:01:49.166 --> 00:01:52.900
Encore, encore, encore!

00:01:52.925 --> 00:01:54.667
- Encore, encore, encore!
- I love you, Naya!

00:02:01.041 --> 00:02:02.291
Thank you.

00:02:04.125 --> 00:02:08.166
A MUSICIAN AND A SONGWRITER.
PERFECTIONIST, BLUNT, AND ANTI-DRAMA.

00:02:08.291 --> 00:02:09.791
Sweetheart.

00:02:11.750 --> 00:02:12.916
What is this?

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:15.666
For your performance
earlier. You killed it.

00:02:15.791 --> 00:02:19.083
Oh, dear. Your eyes look weird.
What did you do?

00:02:20.041 --> 00:02:21.458
- What are you talking about?
- Miss... Thank you.

00:02:21.922 --> 00:02:22.516
Thank you.

00:02:22.541 --> 00:02:23.791
Bring it to her room.

00:02:23.916 --> 00:02:25.208
I told you I quit.

00:02:25.893 --> 00:02:26.917
Where's Lola?

00:02:28.196 --> 00:02:29.321
Your little sister?

00:02:29.541 --> 00:02:32.844
Of course! How many Lola we have in our
team?

00:02:32.869 --> 00:02:34.986
How could you ask something like that?

00:02:35.291 --> 00:02:38.541
Nay, the audience asks for an encore.

00:02:38.666 --> 00:02:41.250
Ask Thomas to sing. I won't do it.

00:02:41.291 --> 00:02:44.083
The contract only states
that I sing several songs. So, no.

00:02:44.344 --> 00:02:47.750
Encore, encore, encore!

00:02:49.916 --> 00:02:53.083
Sir, where's Naya? What should we do?

00:02:53.666 --> 00:02:55.875
- Sir, I talked to Naya.
- Yes?

00:02:55.916 --> 00:02:58.791
She won't sing another song.

00:02:58.875 --> 00:03:00.625
The contract only requires
her to sing five songs.

00:03:02.041 --> 00:03:02.792
Nay.

00:03:04.791 --> 00:03:05.583
Babe.

00:03:05.875 --> 00:03:08.583
Babe? I'm not your babe.

00:03:11.291 --> 00:03:13.333
Nay, there's someone here.

00:03:13.791 --> 00:03:14.900
Meet...

00:03:16.041 --> 00:03:17.416
Uncle Joni.

00:03:18.916 --> 00:03:20.042
Yes, I know.

00:03:20.541 --> 00:03:21.792
Joni Halmalisa?

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:23.791
- Right.
- Yes.

00:03:23.833 --> 00:03:25.750
A LEGENDARY MUSICIAN.
FOUNDER OF THE BATAVIA MELODIES.

00:03:25.791 --> 00:03:29.916
A member of The Batavia Melodies...

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:34.791
...from 1976 to 1982.

00:03:34.875 --> 00:03:36.791
It's 1984.

00:03:36.916 --> 00:03:40.666
But thank you for still remembering me
and liking my songs.

00:03:40.791 --> 00:03:43.333
It's my mom who actually liked you.

00:03:44.666 --> 00:03:46.000
- Please, take a seat.
- Okay.

00:03:46.125 --> 00:03:49.141
What do you want?
We have snacks, tea...

00:03:49.166 --> 00:03:52.541
- Water is good.
- Water, Thomas.

00:03:52.666 --> 00:03:53.875
So, Nay,

00:03:53.980 --> 00:03:57.503
Uncle Joni wants to make a
comeback to the music industry.

00:03:57.625 --> 00:04:00.166
To pay for the electricity bill back home.

00:04:01.202 --> 00:04:03.077
Nay, I have an idea.

00:04:03.166 --> 00:04:05.041
- Come here, Uncle. Sorry.
- Yeah, okay.

00:04:06.625 --> 00:04:10.308
I want to combine an old legend...

00:04:11.159 --> 00:04:12.766
...and a future legend.

00:04:12.791 --> 00:04:15.000
Joni and Naya.

00:04:23.750 --> 00:04:25.483
Here's the thing, Nay.

00:04:25.791 --> 00:04:30.791
We're going to remake
my song called "Your Way".

00:04:30.916 --> 00:04:35.416
I will try to make a new
modern arrangement for it.

00:04:41.750 --> 00:04:43.333
Come with me, Uncle.

00:04:44.166 --> 00:04:47.916
You played it in the key of E, right?
The original was in the key of C, right?

00:04:48.041 --> 00:04:49.125
That's right, Naya.

00:04:49.166 --> 00:04:52.791
I raise the key on purpose
to match your vocal range.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:59.375
Personally, I have no problem with that.
But does it match your vocal range?

00:05:01.750 --> 00:05:03.416
Now, that's it!

00:06:25.916 --> 00:06:33.875
This beautiful song was written
by the living legend, Joni Halmalisa.

00:07:05.250 --> 00:07:06.625
Carry on.

00:07:12.041 --> 00:07:13.791
You two can see it yourselves.

00:07:13.953 --> 00:07:19.119
I can sing any song, better than anyone.

00:07:20.541 --> 00:07:23.125
I don't need anyone. Do you understand?

00:07:23.625 --> 00:07:24.792
Do you understand that too?

00:07:29.291 --> 00:07:31.442
What did you do? Idiot.

00:07:34.500 --> 00:07:37.400
Honestly, I'm fed up with Thomas.

00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:39.833
I think he's still using drugs.

00:07:40.791 --> 00:07:45.291
You should arrange the meeting
with Mr. Indra immediately.

00:07:46.791 --> 00:07:49.166
It should've been done a long time ago.

00:07:49.250 --> 00:07:52.750
Mr. Indra is a greater
producer than Thomas.

00:07:52.791 --> 00:07:55.067
So, make it happen, then.

00:07:55.519 --> 00:07:56.875
- Naya.
- Looks like really hard.

00:07:57.112 --> 00:07:59.266
I have important news.

00:07:59.393 --> 00:08:00.750
Where have you been?

00:08:01.583 --> 00:08:04.541
NAYA'S LITTLE SISTER AND ASSISTANT.
SPONTANEOUS, CLUMSY, ANIMAL LOVER.

00:08:04.625 --> 00:08:06.541
I have important news.

00:08:07.875 --> 00:08:08.875
What?

00:08:08.958 --> 00:08:10.583
It's important.

00:08:10.791 --> 00:08:13.666
Is there something more
important than your work here?

00:08:16.250 --> 00:08:18.125
What are you doing now?

00:08:18.666 --> 00:08:20.292
If I say something, don't get mad.

00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:22.067
Promise me you won't get mad.

00:08:22.541 --> 00:08:23.900
I won't! Move!

00:08:24.541 --> 00:08:25.916
Move.

00:08:33.375 --> 00:08:34.233
Dad?

00:08:49.375 --> 00:08:51.625
Naya, Dad is ill.

00:08:52.041 --> 00:08:53.292
Are you ill?

00:08:54.666 --> 00:08:56.500
You must need money.

00:08:58.416 --> 00:09:02.375
I'm shocked to see you here.

00:09:02.416 --> 00:09:06.041
So, you come here because
you need money, right?

00:09:06.125 --> 00:09:09.166
Wait here for a while,
Dad. La, come with me.

00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:13.750
- What?
- Take him to the ATM.

00:09:13.791 --> 00:09:15.667
After that,

00:09:15.704 --> 00:09:17.100
- give him money to go home. Here.
- ATM?

00:09:17.125 --> 00:09:19.000
- Why?
- He needs money.

00:09:19.041 --> 00:09:21.833
- He's ill. He's...
- Take this.

00:09:22.541 --> 00:09:24.875
- He's...
- Don't be selfish.

00:09:25.375 --> 00:09:29.208
His wife should be the one
who takes care of him. Got it?

00:09:30.125 --> 00:09:30.750
Okay?

00:09:31.791 --> 00:09:33.041
Come on, Dad.

00:09:37.416 --> 00:09:41.291
Keep healthy, Dad.
Don't forget to eat. Sleep well.

00:09:41.316 --> 00:09:42.067
Hey!

00:09:43.375 --> 00:09:45.083
That's my car!

00:09:47.166 --> 00:09:48.750
He remembers his car.

00:09:52.416 --> 00:09:56.192
Yes, this is the one
you left for us to keep.

00:09:56.750 --> 00:09:59.291
I haven't got the chance to thank you.

00:09:59.375 --> 00:10:01.541
Because you left in a hurry.

00:10:03.291 --> 00:10:04.625
Naya...

00:10:04.666 --> 00:10:07.291
Okay, then. I'm going back in.

00:10:07.375 --> 00:10:08.541
- I have another job.
- Wait...

00:10:08.625 --> 00:10:11.500
- Take care of your health.
- What job?

00:10:11.541 --> 00:10:13.416
- Take him.
- Naya...

00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:14.650
Naya!

00:10:15.375 --> 00:10:17.108
Dad, wait here for a minute, okay?

00:10:17.625 --> 00:10:18.400
Naya.

00:10:19.103 --> 00:10:20.170
Do you hear me?

00:10:21.291 --> 00:10:22.358
Naya.

00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:26.625
Dad was dumped by his wife.

00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:38.291
Dumped?

00:10:39.625 --> 00:10:40.942
Dad was dumped?

00:10:43.541 --> 00:10:47.233
His wife dropped him at a nursing home.

00:10:48.541 --> 00:10:49.400
Here.

00:10:49.875 --> 00:10:51.666
She sent this letter.

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:55.483
She said she couldn't
take care of him anymore.

00:10:59.041 --> 00:11:02.416
This is a lesson for you, little sister.

00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:06.041
When you choose a life partner,
what should you do?

00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:09.083
You should be careful.

00:11:11.291 --> 00:11:12.167
Naya.

00:11:23.916 --> 00:11:24.583
Nay?

00:11:27.291 --> 00:11:28.208
Nay, what's wrong?

00:11:32.416 --> 00:11:33.500
What do you need?

00:11:33.541 --> 00:11:35.125
I just need to be alone.

00:11:36.666 --> 00:11:39.000
Sorry about Uncle Joni.

00:11:39.041 --> 00:11:41.000
I was just trying to do my best.

00:11:43.109 --> 00:11:44.416
For your sake, too.

00:11:46.416 --> 00:11:47.400
Drink this.

00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:49.567
To avoid dehydration.

00:12:08.750 --> 00:12:10.733
I need to leave.

00:12:11.041 --> 00:12:13.666
Your mom and I have too much difference.

00:12:18.916 --> 00:12:23.666
Dad!

00:12:23.750 --> 00:12:26.541
Don't leave me!

00:13:03.041 --> 00:13:04.317
Help!

00:13:04.916 --> 00:13:05.900
Help!

00:13:08.666 --> 00:13:09.608
Help!

00:13:15.166 --> 00:13:16.541
Oh, dear! Zul!

00:13:20.166 --> 00:13:22.875
- What did you do to Zul? Hey!
- Nothing.

00:13:22.916 --> 00:13:25.791
- What did you do to Zul?
- Nothing.

00:13:25.916 --> 00:13:28.291
- Zul is dead, Naya!
- I did nothing, Thomas!

00:13:28.416 --> 00:13:31.291
I was down there, asleep! I didn't know!

00:13:31.375 --> 00:13:34.125
- I'm innocent.
- Your clothes are covered in blood!

00:13:42.041 --> 00:13:46.041
Why can't I remember anything?

00:13:46.125 --> 00:13:48.166
Naya? What happened?

00:13:48.291 --> 00:13:49.666
I don't know!

00:13:49.791 --> 00:13:51.791
- Naya, what happened?
- I don't know!

00:13:53.791 --> 00:13:56.291
I can't remember anything.

00:13:56.529 --> 00:13:57.630
Calm down.

00:13:57.655 --> 00:13:59.306
- Do you remember what happened?
- No.

00:13:59.541 --> 00:14:01.458
No, I don't.

00:14:01.791 --> 00:14:03.375
Naya, you must've done something.

00:14:03.416 --> 00:14:04.916
Who else was here, Lola?

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.250
Why are you slandering her like that?

00:14:06.291 --> 00:14:07.791
- Please, Lola.
- What to remember?

00:14:07.875 --> 00:14:09.916
- Try remember...
- She said it wasn't her doing!

00:14:09.941 --> 00:14:11.344
Zul is dead!

00:14:12.125 --> 00:14:14.041
How can she not
remember that Zul died here?

00:14:14.166 --> 00:14:17.416
It's not my doing, Thomas.

00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:19.041
- Try to remember.
- I can't.

00:14:19.166 --> 00:14:21.791
- Naya, no!
- No! I can't!

00:14:21.916 --> 00:14:24.375
- Where are you going?
- I can't be here, Thomas.

00:14:24.416 --> 00:14:26.666
- I can't be here.
- No. Let's call the police first.

00:14:26.791 --> 00:14:28.592
No! You're going to
report me to the police?

00:14:28.616 --> 00:14:30.416
Are you crazy? You
earn your living from me!

00:14:30.500 --> 00:14:32.166
- Everyone, calm down!
- It's a freaking crime scene!

00:14:32.250 --> 00:14:34.416
Everyone, calm down! Can you do that?

00:14:34.541 --> 00:14:36.541
No!

00:14:36.666 --> 00:14:38.416
- I can't be here.
- Naya.

00:14:38.541 --> 00:14:40.375
- Naya!
- No!

00:14:40.416 --> 00:14:42.416
No!

00:14:42.541 --> 00:14:44.250
No, I can't.

00:14:44.291 --> 00:14:46.541
Don't... Naya!

00:14:46.625 --> 00:14:47.791
Naya!

00:14:47.875 --> 00:14:49.166
Naya, wait.

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:51.166
Listen to me first! Naya!

00:14:51.250 --> 00:14:52.916
- Naya.
- Move, Dad.

00:14:53.041 --> 00:14:54.500
- Let Lola drive.
- Okay.

00:14:58.291 --> 00:15:00.541
Lola, why is Dad here?

00:15:00.666 --> 00:15:03.416
You told me to give back the ATM first,
then take him home.

00:15:03.541 --> 00:15:07.416
Get in, hurry. I don't want to be here.
I want to leave. Hurry!

00:15:07.541 --> 00:15:08.541
Where do we go?

00:15:08.625 --> 00:15:10.500
- Just away from here. Can we just go?
- Okay, okay.

00:15:45.416 --> 00:15:47.542
Come on. Let's go home.

00:15:48.166 --> 00:15:49.916
Your mom is waiting.

00:15:50.916 --> 00:15:53.041
Mom? What is he talking about?

00:15:53.166 --> 00:15:54.525
Whose blood is that?

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:56.916
The person who was
stabbed early this evening?

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:59.416
- Huh?
- Wait. Dad.

00:16:00.791 --> 00:16:03.375
- The person who was stabbed early this evening?
- Did you see it?

00:16:03.625 --> 00:16:07.166
Was the person tall? How did they look?

00:16:12.666 --> 00:16:14.916
How did they look? The stabber
and the one who was stabbed?

00:16:16.041 --> 00:16:18.625
- How did the person look like?
- Please, Dad.

00:16:18.666 --> 00:16:22.041
If you know anything, tell me, please.

00:16:22.166 --> 00:16:24.666
- Mr. Thomas.
- Sir!

00:16:24.750 --> 00:16:26.666
Enough. Enough for today.

00:16:26.791 --> 00:16:28.750
And I want to advise Naya...

00:16:28.791 --> 00:16:30.375
Please, come home.

00:16:30.416 --> 00:16:32.541
And to all Indonesian people...

00:16:32.625 --> 00:16:34.750
...if you know Naya's whereabout...

00:16:34.791 --> 00:16:36.166
...please report it.

00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:40.291
You know, then. Please, tell me.
The clothes, what did the person wear?

00:16:43.500 --> 00:16:46.000
Naya, Dad is ill.

00:16:47.125 --> 00:16:48.625
What is his illness?

00:16:50.541 --> 00:16:51.791
Alzheimer.

00:16:53.916 --> 00:16:54.608
Huh?

00:16:55.000 --> 00:17:01.791
I will reward ten million rupiah in cash
for the information.

00:17:01.875 --> 00:17:03.541
Why didn't you tell me?

00:17:03.666 --> 00:17:06.291
I wanted to tell you, but you scolded me.

00:17:06.375 --> 00:17:08.750
We need to go to the
pharmacy to get some medicine.

00:17:08.791 --> 00:17:10.291
Alzheimer isn't like flu.

00:17:10.375 --> 00:17:14.791
But still, there must be some medicine.
Just look for it on Google or something.

00:17:17.541 --> 00:17:20.000
Did you really see it?

00:17:20.041 --> 00:17:21.666
I have a bad feeling.

00:17:21.750 --> 00:17:24.375
Thomas is very suspicious.

00:17:24.416 --> 00:17:27.041
To you, everyone is suspicious.

00:17:27.166 --> 00:17:30.541
Seriously, I really have
a bad feeling this time.

00:17:30.625 --> 00:17:33.291
Why would Thomas say that to the media?

00:17:33.416 --> 00:17:35.666
Being an attention-seeker
isn't against the law, you know.

00:17:38.416 --> 00:17:41.416
You really saw someone getting stabbed?

00:17:41.541 --> 00:17:43.666
Please, Dad, try to remember.

00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:46.166
"A familiar environment."

00:17:49.666 --> 00:17:55.000
"An Alzheimer's patient's memory
can be improved by a familiar environment."

00:17:58.541 --> 00:18:01.291
Dad, where did you live
before the nursing home?

00:18:04.875 --> 00:18:08.041
Seriously, he can't even
remember where he lived?

00:18:08.125 --> 00:18:11.041
Your ID. Ask for his ID.

00:18:13.921 --> 00:18:14.900
Singalaya.

00:18:16.791 --> 00:18:18.291
That's...

00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:25.125
My beautiful audience!

00:18:25.166 --> 00:18:28.291
Why do you answer me? You're not beautiful!

00:18:28.416 --> 00:18:30.041
Don't go home just yet...

00:18:30.125 --> 00:18:34.041
...because Tata will open herself!

00:18:35.125 --> 00:18:37.666
Hey! Somad is here!

00:18:37.791 --> 00:18:39.166
Hey, Somad!

00:18:39.250 --> 00:18:40.666
Give us some tip money...

00:18:40.791 --> 00:18:43.541
...since your wife just
got back from Malaysia.

00:18:43.666 --> 00:18:45.416
Hey!

00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:47.416
For Tata.

00:18:47.541 --> 00:18:48.791
Only 5 thousand?

00:18:48.916 --> 00:18:51.291
Don't you have anything less?

00:18:51.375 --> 00:18:53.625
Come home!

00:18:53.666 --> 00:18:55.541
How could you tip them?

00:18:59.666 --> 00:19:01.875
Sir, excuse me.

00:19:02.916 --> 00:19:03.900
Yes?

00:19:04.250 --> 00:19:06.416
Do you know where Mrs. Lastri lives?

00:19:06.541 --> 00:19:08.041
Which one is Mrs. Lastri?

00:19:08.166 --> 00:19:09.817
Mrs. Lastri, Mr. Anwar's wife.

00:19:10.166 --> 00:19:12.041
- This is Mr. Anwar.
- He's Mr. Anwar.

00:19:12.125 --> 00:19:15.041
I have the address. You can look at it.

00:19:18.791 --> 00:19:20.541
Oh, this man.

00:19:20.625 --> 00:19:24.375
His house... Just go straight,
go pass a dangdut show...

00:19:24.416 --> 00:19:26.291
...go straight until you reach the end,
then turn right.

00:19:30.625 --> 00:19:33.375
Give a round of applause to Tata!

00:19:36.291 --> 00:19:38.666
Make some noise for Tata!

00:19:42.125 --> 00:19:43.916
Give her encouragement!

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:47.291
Tata!

00:20:32.791 --> 00:20:35.000
Forget the price of rice!

00:20:42.166 --> 00:20:43.166
Geez!

00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:52.125
Ria Buana!

00:20:52.166 --> 00:20:54.125
Ria Buana!

00:20:58.291 --> 00:21:00.125
Where did you learn that?

00:21:04.916 --> 00:21:06.166
Hey!

00:21:07.750 --> 00:21:08.916
Stop messing around!

00:21:08.992 --> 00:21:09.924
Sit!

00:21:10.151 --> 00:21:11.055
Calm down.

00:21:11.166 --> 00:21:13.916
What are you doing? You can't just do that.

00:21:14.041 --> 00:21:15.541
Go on!

00:21:15.625 --> 00:21:17.416
She can't do that.

00:21:38.666 --> 00:21:40.916
Is this really the house?

00:21:41.041 --> 00:21:43.541
According to his ID, this is it.

00:21:43.625 --> 00:21:46.291
Melati Street number 20, this is the house.

00:21:53.416 --> 00:21:55.291
THIS HOUSE IS FOR SALE

00:21:58.791 --> 00:22:00.625
The door is locked.

00:22:02.500 --> 00:22:04.291
Why are we here?

00:22:04.416 --> 00:22:05.791
I want to go home!

00:22:05.986 --> 00:22:07.611
This is your house.

00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:12.125
He means our house in Jakarta.

00:22:12.416 --> 00:22:14.750
Your poor mother is waiting!

00:22:18.500 --> 00:22:20.608
She only pities Mom now.

00:22:20.875 --> 00:22:22.525
What about all the time before?

00:22:29.041 --> 00:22:33.041
Lola, we have to live here now!

00:22:33.125 --> 00:22:35.483
